Detailed Description

Enqueues chunks of data (from various sources -- application crashes, kernel log records, etc.).

Defines a filterable behavior.

A helper class for accessing the raw data in the intent extra and handling certificates.

A class containing constants in the MTP and PTP specifications.

The queue is size bounded and will drop old data if the enqueued data exceeds the maximum size. You can think of this as a persistent, system-wide, blob-oriented "logcat".

You can obtain an instance of this class by new DropBoxManager(Context).

DropBoxManager entries are not sent anywhere directly, but other system services and debugging tools may scan and upload entries for processing.

A filterable class can have its data constrained by a filter.

See also:
